        <p><strong>Ext JS</strong> is a pure <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('JavaScript', 'L'); ?> application framework for building interactive web applications using techniques such as <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('AJAX', 'WD'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('DHTML', 'WD'); ?> and DOM scripting.</p>
        <p>Originally built as an add-on library extension of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('YUI', 'JSF'); ?> by <strong>Jack Slocum</strong>, Ext JS includes interoperability with <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('jQuery', 'JS'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Prototype', 'JSF'); ?>. Beginning with version 1.1, Ext JS retains no dependencies on external libraries, instead making their use optional.</p>
